(814,164,"tab_text_content_1","<h3>Chad Van Handel</h3>\r\n<b>Certifications:</b> ASE Master Technician\r\n\r\n<b>Hobbies:</b> Hunting and fishing\r\n\r\n<b>Job Title:</b> Owner, ASE Master Technician ASE, Certified Master Technician\r\n\r\nChad Van Handel was born and raised in La Grande Oregon. You might say he followed in his fathers footsteps and acquired a career in auto motive repair. It started in high school where he was involved with 3 years of automotive technology. After high school Chad attended and graduated from Chemeketa Community College where he obtained a technical degree of applied science in Automotive Technology. Chad was then hired by Capital Auto Group in Salem, Oregon where he served as a technician repairing vehicles. Spending 15 years at Capital, Chad obtained multiple certifications."),
(815,164,"_tab_text_content_1","field_5a6acca1962f8"),
(816,164,"tab_text_content_2","<h3>Tom Van Handel</h3>\r\n<b>Certifications:</b> ASE Certified Technician\r\n\r\n<b>Hobbies:</b> Hunting and fishing\r\n\r\n<b>Job Title:</b> Technician and Mechanic and Awesome Grandfather\r\n\r\nToms desire to start a career in automotive repair began during his high school years in LaGrande Oregon while attempting to keep his MGA on the road. He spent many hours in auto shop class learning theory and basic skills.\r\n\r\nAfter graduating from Denver Automotive and Diesel College in 1973, Tom married Cheryl and has remained happily married to her ever since.\r\n\r\nFor the next 24 years after college, Tom was employed at Lynch Motor Co. (GM dealer) in LaGrande as a technician and later as a service manager. During this time he raised three children while working through years of technological changes and completed numerous factory training courses as well as management training.\r\n\r\nTom and Cheryl moved to Central Oregon after their kids had grown up. Tom began working at the former Sisters Car Care in 2000 as a technician/manager. In the years following, Tom has become a grandfather to four terrific grandchildren. In March of 2007, Tom and Cheryl purchased the business and renamed it Van Handel Automotive Inc. Tom continues to work as a technician/owner and enjoys the challenges of todays auto repair."),
(817,164,"_tab_text_content_2","field_5a6acceb962fc"),
(818,164,"tab_text_content_3","<h3>Brian Chapman</h3>\r\n<b>Certifications:</b> ASE Parts Technician\r\n\r\n<b>Hobbies:</b> Spending time with his family\r\n\r\n<b>Job Title:</b> Service Manager\r\n\r\nBrian has been an experienced parts person for more than twenty years. Familiar with the local dealers and parts houses, Brian is able to procure even the most obscure part with ease while limiting down-time that may effect the ability for our customers to receive their vehicle in a timely manner. Working through these facilities, Brian is able to find the best parts at the best prices. Costly repairs can be minimized with routine maintenance and early diagnosis. There is no more appropriate saying than an ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure."),
